-- Hudaco Climbs to Highest Since 2007 on Increase in Earnings
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-01-10T16:07:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/hudaco-climbs-to-10-month-high-on-expected-increase-in-earnings.html
Hudaco Industries Ltd. (HDC) , a
distributor of industrial products, climbed to its highest since
September 2007 in Johannesburg trading after saying earnings per
share for the 12 months through November will be as much as 40
percent higher than a year earlier.  Shares closed 5.6 percent up at 90.03 rand, the biggest
gain in more than two months.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  